ript type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How do telehealth video consultations work in the Virtual Practice?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Patients book and pay for video visits through your portal or mobile app. At the scheduled time, they log in and join securely. Providers see the appointment in their calendar, access the patient's health record during the call, take notes, and create consultation documents, prescriptions, or lab orders afterward."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do patients and providers receive reminders about video consultations?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Automated reminders are sent for scheduled telemedicine appointments, payments, and follow-ups. Both patients and providers receive notifications by email, SMS, or push — reducing no-shows and keeping everyone prepared."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do patients need special apps for telemedicine visits?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. Patients simply log in through your branded patient portal or mobile app. Telehealth video consultations run directly inside the Virtual Practice platform — no third-party downloads required."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I bill for telehealth visits the same way as in-person consultations?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Telemedicine appointments are defined just like in-person services. You can set duration, service charges, and taxes. Patients pay online, and billing records are automatically generated."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What happens to notes from a video consultation?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Notes taken during the video consultation are stored in the encounter log. Providers can use them to generate consultation documents, prescriptions, or lab orders. If AI Scribe is used, these notes are included as context for creating smarter clinical documentation."}},{"@type":"Ques